{
  "texts": [
    "Several studies found smaller LLMs generally incapable of social reasoning requiring ToM (Sap et al., 2022; van Duijn et al., 2023; Kosinski, 2023).",
    "Larger systems like GPT-4 were discovered to be quite capable at some ToM tasks 9 with a performance at or above children's level of reasoning (Kosinski, 2023; van Duijn et al., 2023).",
    "What is problematic is that this performance significantly suffers when models are presented with adversarial examples (Ullman, 2023; van Duijn et al., 2023; Shapira et al., 2023).",
    "That suggests LLMs do not have a general ability to engage in social reasoning.",
    "However, as van Duijn et al. (2023) noted, we are still in the early stages of testing the social reasoning of LLMs: the fact that they perform well at some ToM tasks should not be discounted."
  ]
}